## WHAT WOULD FALSIFY THIS CLAIM

*Listed in order of falsifying power:*

1. **If a within-sample study manipulates aspect-marking (LE-marked vs. bare versions of the Gödel case presented to Mandarin speakers) and shows NO significant difference in response distributions**, the aspect-marking mechanism is not operative, and the effect must be driven by something else (definiteness, response-style, or an unidentified factor). This is a direct test and would be highly falsifying.

