- **Developmental evidence supports cognitive-style over pure linguistic accounts.** Cross-cultural differences in the Gödel case appear as early as age seven (Machery et al. 2004; extended in Machery 2015), too early to attribute entirely to linguistic category acquisition or university-level WEIRD sampling, and consistent with earlier-developing differences in pragmatic reasoning styles.

