If the effect were driven by grammatical definiteness, Institute 1 predicts greater optionality in the forms used to represent definite NPs in Mandarin than in some existing characterizations, with alternations between definite bare nouns and demonstrative-marked nouns affected by issues of discourse coherence and parsing expectations. But even with that optionality, the grammar does not determine **which description is salient as a candidate referent**—discourse structure does.

