- **Priority 6: Process tracing via think-aloud protocols.** Recruit 30–40 Mandarin and English speakers. Have them complete the Gödel probe while verbalizing their reasoning. Code for mentions of: (a) Schmidt as a potential referent; (b) brute-fact vs. social-fact reasoning; (c) perspective-taking ("What would the people in the story think?"). This qualitative evidence can identify which mechanism is psychologically active during the decision.

