1. **Conduct direct reframing experiments:** Present English-speaking and Mandarin-speaking participants with three versions of the Gödel case: (a) standard (proper name as topic), (b) reframed to ask about the description, (c) reframed to ask about two competing descriptions. Measure whether the cross-cultural effect persists across framings.

