## Key reasons and evidence

- **The Gödel effect is real and replicable.** Machery, Mallon, Nichols & Stich (2004): 56% of Western participants vs. 31% of East Asian participants gave Kripkean responses. The effect persists in native-language presentations (Mandarin Chinese, ~25–30 percentage point difference), ruling out a pure artifact of English article-reading (Machery, Deutsch & Sytsma 2015).

