**From experimental philosophy** (Machery et al., Sytsma & Livengood): The original effect is robust but ambiguity matters. The field has settled on "there are cross-cultural differences in reference intuitions, but the mechanism is contested and linguistic confounds are real." This is conservative wisdom.

