Responses from individuals of East-Asian heritage tend to be more ambivalent and moderate, and these stylistic differences may contaminate substantive conclusions about cultural differences. Individuals from Asian countries tend to respond in the middle response style by selecting anchors in the middle of the Likert scale. 

