- **Map the case-space of naming probes.** Systematically vary the structural features of naming cases (wrong identification, discoverer-namer split, multiple plausible descriptions, prestige asymmetry) and measure which features independently predict cross-cultural divergence. This will clarify whether the Gödel effect is case-specific or representative of a broader class.

